<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>To install a theme, add this to your compass.rb file:

  ## This assumes '.'
  require 'compass-wordpress'

  ## An alternate command to run:
  compass -r compass-wordpress -f wordpress --sass-dir=sass --css-dir=css -s compressed -p &lt;Theme Name&gt; /path/to/installation

What this does is call compass, requires the compass-wordpress extension, uses the framework wordpress, sets the sass and css directories, sets the Sass output to be compressed and finally ends with you setting the theme name.</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
